  "description": [
    "TWENTYNINTH CONGRESS FIRST SESSION Wednesday January 7 1846 IN SENATE The VICE PRESIDENT laid before the Senate a com munication from the War Department exhibiting agreeably to law the contracts made under the authority of that De partment for the last year Also a report from the Secretary of the Treasury com municating information in regard to the expediency of erect ing a light on the stone pier in the Delaware river which was referred to the Committee on Commerce and ordered to be printed Mr BAGBY was excused from serving as Chairman of the Committee of Claims Mr CALHOUN rose to ask a similar favor Finding that in his absence he had been appointed Chairman of the Com mittee on Finance he was under the necessity of asking the indulgence of the Senate He would be exceedingly glad if the state of things permitted to render all the service in his power but he had several reasons for desiring to be excused one of which he would assign and he believed it would be sufficient to satisfy the Senate that he ought to be excused The business to be transacted by that committee would be very extensive and would"
  ],
